---
title: Tab Navigation
description: Tabbed interface using radio inputs and the `:checked` pseudo-class.
slug: tab-navigation
cssFile: tab-navigation.css
explanation: Hidden radio inputs store which tab is active. Because only one radio per group can be checked at a time, CSS can target the correct panel and <code>&lt;label&gt;</code> using the sibling combinator. Each <code>&lt;input&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;label&gt;</code>, and panel need matching <code>id</code>/<code>for</code> attributes and sibling relationships in the DOM.
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="tabs">
	<input class="tab-inputs" type="radio" name="tabs" id="demo-tab-navigation-t1" checked>
	<input class="tab-inputs" type="radio" name="tabs" id="demo-tab-navigation-t2">
	<input class="tab-inputs" type="radio" name="tabs" id="demo-tab-navigation-t3">
	<div class="tab-labels">
		<label class="tab-label" for="demo-tab-navigation-t1">Design</label>
		<label class="tab-label" for="demo-tab-navigation-t2">Code</label>
		<label class="tab-label" for="demo-tab-navigation-t3">Preview</label>
	</div>
	<div class="tab-panels">
		<div class="tab-panel" id="demo-tab-navigation-p1">Design panel content goes here.</div>
		<div class="tab-panel" id="demo-tab-navigation-p2">Code panel content goes here.</div>
		<div class="tab-panel" id="demo-tab-navigation-p3">Preview panel content goes here.</div>
	</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<div class="tabs">
  <input type="radio" name="tabs" id="t1" checked>
  <input type="radio" name="tabs" id="t2">
  <div class="tab-labels">
    <label for="t1">Tab One</label>
    <label for="t2">Tab Two</label>
  </div>
  <div class="tab-panels">
    <div class="tab-panel" id="p1">Content 1</div>
    <div class="tab-panel" id="p2">Content 2</div>
  </div>
</div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
input[type="radio"] { display: none; }

.tab-labels {
  display: flex;
  border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e2e8;
}

label {
  padding: .6rem 1.1rem;
  cursor: pointer;
  border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
  margin-bottom: -2px;
}

.tab-panel { display: none; }

#t1:checked ~ .tab-labels label[for="t1"],
#t2:checked ~ .tab-labels label[for="t2"] {
  color: #5b4cdb;
  border-bottom-color: #5b4cdb;
}

#t1:checked ~ .tab-panels #p1,
#t2:checked ~ .tab-panels #p2 {
  display: block;
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
